<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-02-03T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-02-03T15:00:00-05:00" n="678" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d678">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/5737: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in China (<persName type="to">Johnson</persName>)</hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-02-03T15:00:00-05:00">February 3, 1933—3
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>37. Your 107, February 2, 2 p.m. The Department is studying this matter
                            and desires to receive as soon as practicable a telegraphic report
                            giving the Legation’s views and recommendations.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>